{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"67012bd8-5000-45cd-a8eb-5c9323cc3a10","content":"Use **`dotnet test`**, not `dotnet run`.\n\nThe `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package integrates with the **Microsoft Testing Platform**. When you run `dotnet test`, it watches for file changes and re-runs affected tests automatically — no need for `dotnet run` or `dotnet watch`.\n\nJust make sure:\n- The `TESTINGPLATFORM_HOTRELOAD_ENABLED` environment variable is set to `1`.\n- You have `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` set to `true` (you already do, line 5).\n\nThen simply run:\n```\ndotnet test\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c9681a8c-d565-4334-b401-453881eeb457","outputTokens":152,"requestId":"0427:28DE61:1A0C4EB:1D894BE:69E8242D"},"id":"969658f0-2736-4ab9-87be-5653d807170c","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:28:18.391Z","parentId":"078a983f-5972-4ecc-9a42-cb2bab603ed1"}
